An Act to prevent predatory towing fees for police-authorized tows.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1:
2 Establishment of Approved Towing and Storage Fees
3 1. The Department of Utilities shall establish a list of approved charges for towing and
4 storage services provided by towing companies contracted by state or local police departments.
5 2. The list of approved charges shall include, but not be limited to, the following:
6 a. Maximum fees for towing services, based on vehicle size and weight.
7 b. Maximum fees for storage services, based on the length of time the vehicle is stored.
8 c. Maximum fees for additional services, such as winching, dolly fees, or special
9 equipment
1 of 3

10 fees.
11 3. The list of approved charges shall be reviewed and updated by the Department of
12 Utilities at least once every two years to ensure that it remains reflective of current market
13 conditions.
14 4. The Department of Utilities shall make the list of approved charges publicly available
15 on its website and provide copies to all towing companies contracted by state or local police
16 departments.
17 SECTION 2:
18 Compliance and Enforcement
19 1. All towing companies contracted by state or local police departments shall adhere to
20 the list of approved charges established pursuant to Section 1 of this Act when invoicing vehicle
21 owners for towing and storage services.
22 2. Any towing company found to be in violation of this Act shall be subject to a penalty
23 for each offense.
24 3. The Department of Utilities shall have the authority to investigate complaints of
25 violations of this Act and may inspect the records of any towing company contracted by state or
26 local police departments to ensure compliance.
27 4. The Department of Utilities shall have the authority to suspend or revoke the contract
28 of any towing company found to be in repeated or willful violation of this Act.
