29 5. The Department of Utilities shall promulgate regulations to implement the provisions
30 of this Act.
31 6. Nothing in this Act shall be construed to limit or restrict the authority of any law
32 enforcement agency to tow or impound vehicles pursuant to existing law. Typically, the effective
33 date of a legislative bill is determined based on various factors, such as the complexity of the
34 implementation process, the need for regulatory rule-making or other administrative actions, and
35 the need for public awareness or education.
36 The bill takes effect 90 or 120 days after passage, to allow for administrative
37 implementation.
